Sleep paralysis is a state, during waking up or falling asleep, in which a person is aware but unable to move or speak.  During an episode, one may hallucinate (hear, feel, or see things that are not there), which often results in fear.  Episodes generally last less than a couple of minutes.  It may occur as a single episode or be recurrent.
Between 8% and 50% of people experience sleep paralysis at some point in their life.  About 5% of people have regular episodes.  Males and females are affected equally.  Sleep paralysis has been described throughout history.

Instantly my eyes started watering and it was a very very uncomfortable feeling. My eyes were watering for 6 hours after the test due to them ramming that in my brain. I will know the results of my test within 5-7 days and I will keep you guys updates. I feel a lot better today and feel like normal. For those of you not taking this serious you really need to reconsider the damage that this has done to the world and can do to your loved ones. Please stay inside and please stay safe. My breathing is back to normal and I am starting to get my appetite back and feeling better. I will let you guys know the results when I get them back. Thanks for reading!
